label: segmental pulmonary vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the main pulmonary veins and drains oxygenated blood from a segment of the lung.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: subsegmental pulmonary vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the segmental pulmonary veins and drains oxygenated blood from a subsegment of the lung.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: esophageal vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the azygos vein and drains blood from the esophagus.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: supreme intercostal vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the superior intercostal vein and drains the first intercostal space.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: lateral sacral vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the internal iliac vein and drains the anterior surface of the sacrum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: middle hemorrhoidal vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the internal iliac vein.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: uterine vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the internal iliac vein and drains the uterus.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: deep cervical vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of a vertebral vein and drains the suboccipital region, adjacent vertebral column, and deep muscles of the neck.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: intra-acinar venule
definition: A venule that receives drainage from the capillary beds after blood has perfused the pulmonary alveoli, and is tributary of the pulmonary venules.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: lateral femoral circumflex vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the femoral vein and drains blood from the front and middle areas of the thigh.
synonym: set of lateral circumflex femoral veins
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: basivertebral vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the anterior internal vertebral venous plexus and drains blood from the vertebral bodies.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: bronchial venule
definition: A venule that is tributary of the bronchial veins and drains blood from the bronchi and bronchioles of the lungs.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: mental vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the facial vein and drains blood from the chin and lower lip.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: deep lingual vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the lingual vein and drains blood from the tongue.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: dorsal lingual vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the lingual vein and drains blood from the dorsum of the tongue, and the sides of the tongue.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: sublingual vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the lingual vein and drains blood from the ventral (inferior) surface of the tongue and the sublingual glands.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: glandular venous plexus
definition: A venous plexus tha connects the middle and superior thyroid veins.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: circumflex humeral vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the axillary vein and drains blood from the region around the neck of the humerus.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: thoracoacromial vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the axillary vein and drains blood from the thoracoacromial region, including the pectoral, shoulder, and clavicular regions.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: transverse cervical vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the external jugular vein and drains blood from the superficial muscles of the back, mainly the trapezius muscle.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: suboccipital venous plexus
definition: A venous plexus that is tributary of the deep cervical veins and drains blood from the suboccipital region.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: superficial iliac circumflex vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the great saphenous vein and drains blood from the inguinal region and the anterior abdominal wall.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: fibular vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the posterior tibial vein and drains blood from the lateral compartment of the leg.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: prostatic venule
definition: A venule that is tributary of the prostatic venous plexus and drains blood from the prostate gland.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: hepatic portal venule
definition: A venule that branches from the hepatic portal vein to transport nutrient-rich blood from the gastrointestinal tract and spleen to supply the liver. The hepatic portal venule is tributary of the hepatic sinusoids.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: external nasal vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the angular vein and drains blood from the superficial tissues and skin of the dorsum (bridge) and ala (wings) of the nose.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: supratrochlear vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the angular vein and drains blood from the muscles and skin of the forehead.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: transverse nasal root vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the angular veins and drains blood from the bridge of the nose.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: hypophyseal vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the cavernous sinus and drains blood from the pituitary gland.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: inferior anastomotic vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the transverse sinus and drains blood from the adjacent cortical regions of the temporal lobe. The inferior anastomotic vein forms an anastomosis (connection) between the superficial middle cerebral vein anteriorly and the transverse sinus posteriorly.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: radial vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the brachial vein and drains blood from the lateral structures of the forearm, carpal and metacarpal bones, joints of the hand, and lateral forearm muscles.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: ulnar vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the brachial vein and drains blood from the hand and medial and posterior aspect of forearm.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: anterior internal vertebral venous plexus
definition: A venous plexus that is tributary of the basivertebral veins and internal vertebral veins, draining blood from the vertebrae and spinal cord. The anterior internal vertebral venous plexus is located within the vertebral canal.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: intervertebral vein
definition: A vein that drains blood from the vertebral column and intervertebral discs. In the neck, it is tributary of into the vertebral veins. In the thorax, it is tributary of the posterior intercostal veins. In the lumbar and sacral regions, it is tributary of the lumbar and lateral sacral veins
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: lumbar vein
definition: A vein that is tributary of the inferior vena cava and drains blood from the posterior abdominal wall and lumbar region.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489
